# Workflow guardrails — Mike / ChatGPT / Cursor / OMNI

Authority:
- [docs/v2/04-ai-development-standards.md](../docs/v2/04-ai-development-standards.md)
- [docs/development/DEV-EXECUTION-AND-PROMOTION-MODEL.md](../docs/development/DEV-EXECUTION-AND-PROMOTION-MODEL.md) — **feature-once DEV execution**

**Mike priority (ad-hoc):** Use **OMNI** for in-Airtable Q&A Mike wants to do himself.

**Approved feature Phase 3:** Cursor/Lead may finish the feature in **DEV autonomously** (fields, formulas, views, fixtures, script repairs) without stopping for routine approvals. Stop only for product decisions, PROD, archive, real sends, or other high-risk triggers in the DEV execution model.

## Every new task (Cursor)

1. Output **Task Classification** first (include Phase, Correct tool, Repo, Mike's role).
2. If outside Cursor scope, output **Workspace Check** and redirect — do not proceed silently.
3. If Phase 3 with approved feature brief: execute to DEV Definition of Done; one consolidated report at the end — not an approval per repair.

## Redirect (do not implement here)

| Request | Send to |
|---------|---------|
| Ad-hoc views/formulas/data Mike wants to explore himself | **OMNI** (Mike in base) |
| Planning, requirements, copy, Phase 4 review | **ChatGPT** |
| Code/audits/commits with no backlog ID or unapproved feature brief | Stop — ask Mike for ID + outcome + acceptance criteria |
| Backlog edits | `docs/v2-change-backlog.md` only (not Master Plan Brief) |
| Hoop landing, JR Ref | Wrong repo — not `127-si-shooting-challenge` |
| PROD promotion / archive write / real family sends | Stop — Mike approval |

## Cursor scope only

Phase 3 (Implementation) and Phase 5 (Close). `airtable/`, `web/`, `tools/`, `make/`, audits, commits when Mike asks — or when completing an **approved** feature end-to-end in DEV.

**DEV promotion package:** Before calling a feature done, prepare prod steps in `docs/deploy-checklists/` (DEV execution model §4–§6). Undocumented DEV work is not promotion-ready.

## Workspace Check template

```
Workspace Check
You are in the wrong area if you proceed here.
Current request:
Correct phase:
Correct tool:
Correct repo:
What Mike should do instead:
What to open / paste:
```
